Market Definition

Ocular pain which is also known as eye pain, usually occurs due to mild irritation, but it is rarely a symptom of a serious condition. Normally the pain gets subsided without medicine or further treatment, and recovers automatically by the self-immune system. Although, ocular pain having primary ophthalmic disorders requires timely treatment. Often ocular pain is treated with eye drops and topical steroids or NSAIDs.

